	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87582><span id= >Autrus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>4 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Don't forget Bards, charisma is just as important to them as it is to enchanters.&nbsp;&nbsp;If not more so...  Why is it more important u ask?..Well lets just say the bard is being used for crowd control.. With the bards mez only lasting 15seconds, he must have as little resisted mezzes as possible, if 2 gets resisted in the 15 second cycle, the bard is going to get behind in it (figuring he is keeping 4 mezzed).  Hence it is crucial for the bard not to get resisted, an enchanter has much more opportunity (ie. time) to re-mez..<br><br>Wiever<br>54 Bard </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
